      "url": "https://www.amazon.com/Battle-Christmas-Reign-Nutcrackers/dp/B0DPKHMYZ1",
      "keywords": "Christmas, holiday fiction, Christmas adventure, family story, Christmas magic, nutcracker, holiday reading, Christmas novel, festive fiction",
      "audience": {
        "@type": "Audience",
        "audienceType": "Family audience, children and adults"
      },
      "inLanguage": "en-US",
      "review": {
        "@type": "Review",
        "reviewRating": {
          "@type": "Rating",
          "ratingValue": "5"
        },
        "author": {
          "@type": "Person",
          "name": "Amazon Reader"
        },
        "reviewBody": "I decided to give this book a try over the holiday season and I'm so glad I did! This was a huge break from the normal self-help / non-fiction books I like to read, so I wasn't sure what to expect. The authors do a wonderful job of building a world based on their own lives while pushing into fantasy and adventure in so many creative ways! I couldn't put the book down after the halfway point where the story keeps you guessing while filling you with an undeniable Christmas cheer. I'm a grown adult who felt like a kid again while enjoying this story."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Book",
      "@id": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/work#escape-from-browns-island",
      "name": "Escape from Browns Island",
      "author": [
        {
          "@type": "Person",
          "name": "Zach Hawrot",
          "url": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/authors/zach"
        },
        {
          "@type": "Person",
          "name": "Josh Hawrot",
          "url": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/authors/josh"
        }
      ],
      "genre": ["Young Adult", "YA Fiction", "Teen Fiction", "Adventure Fiction", "Supernatural Fiction", "Coming of Age"],
      "bookFormat": "https://schema.org/EBook",
      "description": "Every small town has legends—but not every kid gets the chance to rewrite them. This novelette starts off with a simple dare: 17-year-old Tommy must spend one summer night alone on Browns Island, an abandoned, 4-mile-long island in the heart of the Ohio River. What he wants is a peaceful night to himself. What he needs is an escape from the chaos he just caused his family. What he finds is an island that isn't abandoned. It is alive and waiting for his arrival.",
      "image": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/assets/brownsisland.jpg",
      "url": "https://dub.sh/browns-island",
      "keywords": "young adult, YA fiction, teen fiction, adventure, supernatural, coming of age, Ohio River, small town, legends, teenage protagonist",
      "audience": {
        "@type": "Audience",
        "audienceType": "Young Adult",
        "suggestedMinAge": 13,
        "suggestedMaxAge": 18
      },
      "inLanguage": "en-US",
      "numberOfPages": "Novelette length",
      "review": {
        "@type": "Review",
        "reviewRating": {
          "@type": "Rating",
          "ratingValue": "5"
        },
        "author": {
          "@type": "Person",
          "name": "Amazon Reader"
        },
        "reviewBody": "Escape from Brown's Island bursts off the page like a star running back on a Saturday-night breakaway—fast, thrilling, and impossible to stop. The Hawrot siblings cut, juke, and power through danger with the perfect mix of grit and finesse, turning every chapter into a game-winning drive."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Book",
      "@id": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/work#wild-adventure-mitch",
      "name": "The Wild Adventure of Mitch and the Sand Bridge",
      "author": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Zach Hawrot",
        "url": "https://www.siblingswrite.com/authors/zach"
      },
      "genre": ["Middle Grade", "Children's Fiction", "Adventure Fiction", "Summer Reading"],
      "description": "Welcome to summer vacation! The time for good memories, great beaches, and — invasions?",
      "url": "https://www.amazon.com/Wild-Adventure-Mitch-Sand-Bridge-ebook/dp/B0CJKVK2ZD",
      "keywords": "middle grade, children's adventure, summer vacation, beach story, middle grade fiction",
      "audience": {
        "@type": "Audience",
        "audienceType": "Middle Grade",
        "suggestedMinAge": 8,
        "suggestedMaxAge": 12
      },
      "inLanguage": "en-US"
    }
  ]
